….Dedicates the award to his Distinguished colleagues in Senate By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  Presidentt of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan was on Sunday night awarded the 2019 Zik Prize in Political Leadership. Lawan’s Chief of Staff, Dr Babagana Muhammad-Aji was at the impressive ceremony in Lagos to receive the award on behalf of the Senate President. According to the statement signed by the Special Adviser (Media) to President of the Senate, Ola Awoniyi, the organisers of the award, the Public Policy Research and Analysis Centre(PPRAC) said Lawan’s consideration was in recognition of his “long-standing dynamic service to the Nigerian state” and his “undying  commitment to the entrenchment of democratic ideals in the Nigerian polity.”         The Senate President, on behalf of his Distinguished colleagues, once again assured the nation that they would continue to put in their best in the onerous task of nation building.     By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Senate President Ahmad Lawan has approved the appointments of Babagana Muhammad Aji and Festus Adedayo as his Chief of Staff and Special Adviser on Media and Publicity respectively. According to a statement signed by the Special Adviser to the Senate President on Administration,… June 18, 2019 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Group under the aegis of Coalition of United Political Parties (CUPP) has taken the President of the 9th Senate, Senator Ahmed Lawan to the cleaners for sacking his special adviser on media, who is a cerebral media practitioner for mere reason that he… June 21, 2019 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Special Assistant on New Media to the President of the Senate, Sen. Ahmed Lawan, Mr Olu Onemola, has resigned his appointment. A statement by the Special Assistant to Lawan on Media and Publicity, Mr Mohammed Isa, on Sunday in Abuja, said the… June 23, 2019 In "Top Stories"